entries.meaning: (history) The son or male-line grandson of an emperor of the Austro-Hungarian Empire.
examples: World War I traditionally started with the assassination of Archduke Francis (Franz) Ferdinand.

entries.meaning: (history) The ruler of an archduchy, in particular the Archduchy of Austria.
